{"parse":{"title":"Midwestern Universities Research Association","pageid":35026878,"revid":785314933,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Midwestern Universities Research Association</b> (<b>MURA</b>) was a collaboration between 15 universities with the goal of designing and building a <a href=\"/wiki/Particle_accelerator\" title=\"Particle accelerator\">particle accelerator</a> for the <a href=\"/wiki/Midwestern_United_States\" title=\"Midwestern United States\">Midwestern United States</a>. It existed between 1953\u20131967, but could not achieve its goal in this time and lost funding. It was thought that President <a href=\"/wiki/John_F._Kennedy\" title=\"John F. Kennedy\">John F. Kennedy</a> would have supported the MURA machine, while one of President <a href=\"/wiki/Lyndon_B._Johnson\" title=\"Lyndon B. Johnson\">Lyndon B. Johnson</a>'s first actions was the shutdown of the MURA machine and laboratory.<sup id=\"cite_ref-inno_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-inno-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mura_ring.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mura_ring.jpg/220px-Mura_ring.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"202\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mura_ring.jpg/330px-Mura_ring.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mura_ring.jpg/440px-Mura_ring.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"900\" data-file-height=\"825\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mura_ring.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>layout of MURA FFAG</div></div></div>\n<p>In its formative years, <a href=\"/wiki/Donald_Kerst\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Donald Kerst\">Donald Kerst</a> was the director of MURA.<sup id=\"cite_ref-inno_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-inno-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> At this institution, <a href=\"/wiki/Keith_Symon\" title=\"Keith Symon\">Keith Symon</a> invented the <a href=\"/wiki/FFAG_accelerator\" title=\"FFAG accelerator\">FFAG accelerator</a>, independently to <a href=\"/wiki/Tihiro_Ohkawa\" title=\"Tihiro Ohkawa\">Tihiro Ohkawa</a>, which combines several concepts of <a href=\"/wiki/Cyclotron\" title=\"Cyclotron\">cyclotrons</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Synchrotron\" title=\"Synchrotron\">synchrotrons</a>. FFAG concepts were extensively developed in MURA. The proposed MURA accelerators were scaling <a href=\"/wiki/FFAG_synchrotron\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"FFAG synchrotron\">FFAG synchrotrons</a>, meaning that orbits of any momentum are photographic enlargements of those of any other momentum.\n</p><p>The concept of FFAG acceleration was revived in the early 1980s,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and gained interest up to the present day, see e.g. <a href=\"/wiki/EMMA_(accelerator)\" title=\"EMMA (accelerator)\">EMMA (accelerator)</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Midwestern_Universities_Research_Association&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-inno-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-inno_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-inno_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Jones, L.; Mills, F.; Sessler, A.; Symon, K.; Young, D. (2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=Bn7Z4VVB9uUC&amp;pg=PP1\"><i>Innovation was not enough: a history of the Midwestern Universities Research Association (MURA)</i></a>. World Scientific. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789812832832\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9789812832832\">9789812832832</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Innovation+was+not+enough%3A+a+history+of+the+Midwestern+Universities+Research+Association+%28MURA%29&amp;rft.pub=World+Scientific&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=9789812832832&amp;rft.aulast=Jones&amp;rft.aufirst=L.&amp;rft.au=Mills%2C+F.&amp;rft.au=Sessler%2C+A.&amp;rft.au=Symon%2C+K.&amp;rft.au=Young%2C+D.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBn7Z4VVB9uUC%26pg%3DPP1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMidwestern+Universities+Research+Association\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Martin, S.; W\u00fcstefeld, G. (ed.) (1983). <i>Seminar on Fixed Field Alternating Gradient accelerators (FFAG)</i>, held at <a href=\"/wiki/J%C3%BClich_Research_Centre\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"J\u00fclich Research Centre\">J\u00fclich Research Centre</a>. informal collection of contributed talks. KFA report SNQ 2 MZ / BS 001</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Midwestern_Universities_Research_Association&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>F. Cole. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://epaper.kek.jp/c01/cyc2001/extra/Cole.pdf\"><i>O Camelot</i></a>. Supplement to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://accelconf.web.cern.ch/AccelConf/c01/start.html\">Proc. 16th Intl. Conf. on Cyclotrons and their Applications (Cyclotrons 2001)</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd>this paper was published posthumously.</dd></dl>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Jones, L.; Mills, F.; <a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Sessler\" title=\"Andrew Sessler\">Sessler, A.</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/Keith_Symon\" title=\"Keith Symon\">Symon, K.</a>; Young, D. (2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=Bn7Z4VVB9uUC&amp;pg=PP1\"><i>Innovation was not enough: a history of the Midwestern Universities Research Association (MURA)</i></a>. World Scientific. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789812832832\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9789812832832\">9789812832832</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Innovation+was+not+enough%3A+a+history+of+the+Midwestern+Universities+Research+Association+%28MURA%29&amp;rft.pub=World+Scientific&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft.isbn=9789812832832&amp;rft.aulast=Jones&amp;rft.aufirst=L.&amp;rft.au=Mills%2C+F.&amp;rft.au=Sessler%2C+A.&amp;rft.au=Symon%2C+K.&amp;rft.au=Young%2C+D.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBn7Z4VVB9uUC%26pg%3DPP1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMidwestern+Universities+Research+Association\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<dl><dd>A book by MURA veterans that was designed to augment Cole's posthumous manuscript.</dd></dl>\n<ul><li>Daniel S. Greenberg, Chapters X and XI of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=HgbbT1SqTT4C&amp;pg=PA256\">The Politics of Pure Science</a>, Plume Books, 1967, University of Chicago Press, 1999.</li></ul>\n<dl><dd>deals with politics around MURA, particularly the battle over funding higher energy machines being studied at Berkeley and at Brookhaven (New York) and funding MURA, a machine that would produce the same energy as Argonne's Zero Gradient Synchrotron but at 100 fold the intensity.</dd></dl>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:School.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/School.svg/30px-School.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/School.svg/45px-School.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/School.svg/60px-School.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"500\" data-file-height=\"500\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about an education organization is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Midwestern_Universities_Research_Association&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Edu-org-stub\" title=\"Template:Edu-org-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Edu-org-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Edu-org-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Edu-org-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Handshake_(Workshop_Cologne_%2706).jpeg\" clas